

Add policy eksaccesspolicy and paste below:
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "eks:DescribeCluster",
        "eks:ListClusters",
        "eks:DescribeNodegroup",
        "eks:ListNodegroups",
        "eks:ListUpdates",
        "eks:AccessKubernetesApi"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}

Add that policy into ec2management.

attach that ec2management in launch instance.

Install Kubectl:
curl -O https://s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/amazon-eks/1.24.11/2023-03-17/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
chmod +x ./kubectl
sudo cp ./kubectl /usr/local/bin
export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH

kubectl version

Install AWScli:
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install


